    <note>Chen(1) Zhi(2) [7124] His grandfather moved from Changan to Suzhou at the end of the Tang. Zhiwu's [7125] father, husband of Ding(1) Wei's [1641] sister. His four other sons died young. Wang Anshi [1762] drafted the funerary inscriptions for Zhixiang [3054] and Zhiyuan [3058], who died at the respective ages of 32 and 27. The fortunes of the family declined after the death of Zhiwu's son, Bolun [3079]. Suzhou FZ, 76.31a-31b; Wang Anshi, WJ, 93.967, 95.986; YLDD, 2367.13a, 2368.3a.</note>
